## Architecture rules

This project uses reassure taxonomy enforcement. Before writing to any file:

1. Call `get_symbol_map()` to see what already exists
2. Call `get_blast_radius()` before touching shared symbols
3. Respect the layer boundaries enforced by `.reassure.toml`

## Where things go

See `.reassure.toml` for the full ruleset. Short version:

- **UI** — screens/pages only. No business logic, no direct data access.
- **Logic** — services, blocs, notifiers. No UI imports.
- **Data** — repositories only. Owns all network and storage calls.
- **Core** — constants, theme, utils. Keep it small. Lock files when done.

## Do not

- Add business logic to a screen/page
- Import UI packages from a service or repository
- Push past the LoC limits without a good reason — split the file instead
